            <h1>Food, fisheries and agriculture</h1>
            <div class="temaMobIngressImg" style="display: none;"><img src="/Upload/PORTAL/Temabilder/mat_fisk_150x113.jpg" alt="Dishes of food" /></div>
            <p class="textIngress">The Government’s food policy aims to ensure that consumers, as a result of healthy food production, can buy safe and wholesome food of the desired quality. The policy relating to fisheries and the coast aims to contribute to sustainable and environmentally-friendly value creation for the whole of society, while at the same time contributing to a fair distribution of the country’s resources. The Government’s goal is to ensure the continued existence of an active agricultural sector throughout the country.</p>
            <img src="/Upload/PORTAL/Temabilder/mat_fisk_150x113.jpg" alt="Dishes of food" class="temaIngressImg" />
            <div class="descriptionText"><p><em>The Ministry of Agriculture and Food</em> has chief responsibility for food policy and agricultural policy. <em>The Ministry of Fisheries and Coastal Affairs</em> has chief responsibility for fisheries and the aquaculture industry, seafood safety and fish health and welfare. </p>
<p>On this page you will find general information and documents relating to food, fisheries and agriculture. You can explore this topic in more detail by using the menu on the right.</p></div>
